comment.narrative:
(a) 31% (23/72)  of Local Authorities coordinating multi-sectoral HIV&AIDS programmes; 

(b) NAC structure has not been revised to take into account evidence (NASF 2011-2015) and the three (3) ones principles;

(c) 60 % Local/Municipal Authorities with HIV Workplace Policies, Service Directories and Response Committees;

 (d) 86 % of line ministries and national institutions with workplans consisting of costed HIV&AIDS activities;

(e) Partnership strategy for the 2011-2015 NASF has not been developed;

(f) 80 % of NASF budget funded;

(g) Very few lead agencies - ZARAN and NZP+ - (CSOs, Traditional & Faith Based Leaders) have been equipped with skills for mainstreaming human rights for PLHIV.

Some results thus far on the project include:
Database design integrated with secure management of data tools;
System tested and subjected to rigorous business continuity elements;
Political Parties Engaged and resolution to have Political Party IT Experts participate in the orientation process;
Communication Strategy and Engagement Roadmap developed to enhance the visibility of the EIMS;
Other devices for use in areas where there is no GSM coverage tested and the technology (satellite) can work.

The project achieved the following results:
-Reduction in rejected votes from 1.3% in a similar Presidential Election held in 2008 to 1.03%;
-No Presidential petition filed in the courts of law and election result widely accepted;
-81% of disputes resolved by Conflict Management Committees.
